trying to bolster
Assad.

35:35.533 --> 35:44.509 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And what that has meant is
helping the Syrian
regime to bomb the moderate
opposition in

35:44.609 --> 35:55.587 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Syria, which has been putting
pressure on
the Assad regime. That is not
fighting Da'esh,

35:55.687 --> 36:01.926 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and it's taking a toll on the
moderate opposition.
But, you know, the State
Department has a

36:02.027 --> 36:05.597 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
program to work with the
moderate opposition.

36:05.697 --> 36:14.439 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Others around the world,
frankly, in the Middle
East and beyond are working to
try and support

36:14.539 --> 36:19.310 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
