with the Syrian

36:37.095 --> 36:42.767 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
regime and now they're facing
the Russians
working with the Syrian regime,
and they are

36:42.867 --> 36:44.569 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
a resilient bunch.

36:44.669 --> 36:47.338 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: All these
things lead me
to say that we are living
through a period

36:47.439 --> 36:52.310 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
of incredible geopolitical
instability right
now. And part of the reason that
we're aware

36:52.410 --> 36:55.480 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
of that is because of the spread
of digital
technology.

36:55.580 --> 36:58.450 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
One of the concerns that's
always come from
the intelligence community is
that you're

36:58.550 --> 37:03.922 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
not getting enough help from the
technology
companies. So, I wanted to ask,
if you find

37:04.022 --> 37:09.527 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
