accord on
climate change was signed.

41:30.621 --> 41:35.626 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
One of the reasons or one of the
cornerstones
for the success of that accord
was the fact

41:35.727 --> 41:42.233 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
that the U.S. had acted on this
specific policy.
So this is -- as you say, this
is not some

41:42.333 --> 41:48.740 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
small, arcane policy. This was
set to be sort
of the cornerstone of what
President Obama

41:48.840 --> 41:53.044 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
hoped would be the first major
climate action
by the United States.

41:53.144 --> 41:57.982 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: The coal
industry and 20-something
states have been suing to try to
block these

41:58.082 --> 42:01.285 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
